From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kandelo <noreply@kandelo.invalid>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Keep publisher source and trust state immutable

Kandelo's bottle publisher gives Formula evaluation root-owned, read-only
Homebrew source and trust state. Homebrew normally requires its repository to
be writable and persists a redundant per-item trust entry for every fully
qualified install, even when the containing tap is already trusted. Both
behaviors reject the publisher's intentionally immutable state before a
Formula can run.

Exclude only the Homebrew repository from the preinstall writability diagnostic
and skip automatic per-item persistence when the tap already grants the same
authority. Every other required Homebrew path remains subject to the normal
writability check. Explicit `brew trust` operations still use the normal mutation path
and fail against an immutable publisher store. This patch is applied only to
the publisher's temporary Homebrew overlay; guest Homebrew keeps its normal
repository and trust behavior.
---
 Library/Homebrew/diagnostic.rb | 1 +
 Library/Homebrew/trust.rb      | 1 +
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Library/Homebrew/diagnostic.rb b/Library/Homebrew/diagnostic.rb
index 0000000000..0000000000 100644
--- a/Library/Homebrew/diagnostic.rb
+++ b/Library/Homebrew/diagnostic.rb
@@ -408,6 +408,7 @@ module Homebrew
       def check_access_directories
         not_writable_dirs =
           Keg.must_be_writable_directories.select(&:exist?)
+             .reject { |dir| dir == HOMEBREW_REPOSITORY }
              .reject(&:writable?)
         return if not_writable_dirs.empty?

diff --git a/Library/Homebrew/trust.rb b/Library/Homebrew/trust.rb
index 0000000000..0000000000 100644
--- a/Library/Homebrew/trust.rb
+++ b/Library/Homebrew/trust.rb
@@ -121,3 +121,4 @@ module Homebrew
         item_name = ::Utils.name_from_full_name(name)
         tap = Tap.fetch(tap_name)
+        next if trusted_tap?(tap)
         next if tap.official?
